message.content:
cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with network coding and proposes a new class of codes specifically designed to preserve the packet degree distribution during packet encoding, recombination and decoding. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the application of network coding to mobile environments and peer-to-peer mobile media streaming. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes a new approach to controlling and limiting complexity and energy consumption in network coding. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper deals with network coding and its application in distributed systems. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the application of network coding to mobile media streaming.
